        <span title="prefix" class="quotePrefix"></span>
        <span title="quote" class="quoteExact"></span>
        <span title="suffix" class="quoteSuffix"></span>
      
        </div>
        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>Openness lives on a continuum and is not synonymous with no privacy. For me it boils down to learning out loud. Yet an important part of open is being able to control your own dial. </p>
<p>Being open protects the creator and the commons.</p>
<p>Also we have to draw a difference between OER, open research, and open scholarship. Each have consequential implications for the public, the markets and the academies. </p>
        </div>
