          <p>That sound was music to my ears. I am a little younger than danah boyd and was not a tech saavy. I played on Prodigy in middle school. In fact I could not wait to get there during study hall (though spent more time on Carmen San Diego and the Oregon Trail).</p>
<p>Like most people the Internet entered my home through America Online. Then when Netscape dropped and the Web exploded (I was a junior in high school) everything changed, but as boyd points out the social patterns of teens are pretty similar.</p>
