        <span title="suffix" class="quoteSuffix"> Essay authors can receive publi</span>
      
        </div>
        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>The primary difference here is that the site is implementing, and integrating, the tech directly into the page.  Medium is only "annotation" in the sense that it's in the margin-- in all other respects it's simply the same paradigm as the other flavors of web commenting systems, such as Disqus, Livefyre, fb comments, etc.</p>
<p>Web annotation in the sense of the <a href="http://w3.org/annotation">W3C</a> definition is a model where annotation services are provided by third parties and lie elsewhere.  Users invite them to your page, and otherwise they're not visible to other readers who have not done the same.</p>
