        <span title="prefix" class="quotePrefix">07-08) defines picture books as </span>
        <span title="quote" class="quoteExact">"that group of books in which pictures and text are con sidered to be of equal importance</span>
        <span title="suffix" class="quoteSuffix">." Fusion of pictures and text i</span>
      
        </div>
        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>This directly correlates with what I am learning in my EDU305 class.  We talked about how when children are learning to read, they use pictures to facilitate their reading.  This can also be a detriment however, because the child may be reading and they come across a word they don't know that starts with the letter 'o'.  They can look at the picture that has an owl in it and they recognize that owl starts with an "o" and they just guess that the word is owl.  The child never learns to read the word.</p>
        </div>
        <div is="annotation-tags-editor" state="viewing" class="annotationTags" user-can-edit="false" tags="%5B%22edu307%22%5D"><div class="annotationTag"><a target="_tag" href="https://jonudell.info/h/facet/?tag=edu307">edu307</a></div></div>
