        </div>
        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>We collect a lot of data on students. Much of this is in a kind of portfolio of benchmark assessments. Accreditation and practice require this.</p>
<p>Yet these portfolios use what the student did and made not with the student as the main author or audience. They are designed for accreditation not accomplishment.</p>
<p>When we use portfolios in school we too often silo these off and create a closed system. If we are preparing students for a networked society we need to encourage them to grow outward not just inward.</p>
        </div>
