        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>I actually like the distinction "web presence" versus digital citizenship or literacy. It is how we read, write, and participate. The Web is literacy not for literacy. </p>
<p>I like presence because it should be federated and not siloed in a portfolio. It is also a reminder that their is a difference between presence and being present.</p>
<p>We can not let the pursuit of presence hamper our ability to be present.</p>
