        <div class="annotationQuote">
          
        <span title="prefix" class="quotePrefix"></span>
        <span title="quote" class="quoteExact"></span>
        <span title="suffix" class="quoteSuffix"></span>
      
        </div>
        <div class="annotationText">
          <p>Diagnostic assessment is central to early reading instruction. Running records are too often used just to determine a students "level." Instead teachers need to spend more time analyzing patterns in the students mistakes to determine how best to help the student.</p>
<p>For example you might notice students struggling with vowel patterns. You can then create activities to build these skills.</p>
<p>Diagnostic assessments work for phonemic awareness, phonics, and fluency. But there is no diagnostic assessment for vocabulary and reading comprehension.</p>
        </div>
